      <div class="accordion-item open" id="acc-1">
        <button class="accordion-trigger" id="acc-btn-1" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="acc-body-1">
          <h2>What Is the Shopify Automation Scanner?</h2>
          <span class="accordion-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="accordion-body" id="acc-body-1" role="region" aria-labelledby="acc-btn-1">
          <div class="accordion-content" itemprop="text">
            The <strong>Shopify Automation Scanner</strong> is a free diagnostic tool that analyses any public Shopify storefront to identify installed apps, estimate monthly subscription costs, and surface free automation replacements. It works by scanning publicly visible frontend code — no Shopify admin access or login required.
            <br /><br />
            Modern Shopify stores rely on apps for email marketing, analytics, inventory, customer support, reviews, and conversion optimisation. While powerful, these create <strong>recurring SaaS costs</strong> that compound rapidly.
            <br /><br />
            Whether you're auditing your own store or conducting <strong>competitive research</strong>, the scanner delivers an efficiency score, app inventory, estimated monthly spend, and tailored replacement recommendations — all in under 30 seconds. For a deeper per-app verdict, try the <a href="/shopify-app-stack-kill-or-keep-auditor">App Stack Kill-or-Keep Auditor</a> or the <a href="/shopify-app-cost-calculator">App Cost Calculator</a>.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="accordion-item" id="acc-2">
        <button class="accordion-trigger" id="acc-btn-2" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="acc-body-2">
          <h2>How Does the Shopify App Scanner Detect Installed Apps?</h2>
          <span class="accordion-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="accordion-body" id="acc-body-2" role="region" aria-labelledby="acc-btn-2">
          <div class="accordion-content">
            Every Shopify store loads scripts, widgets, and tracking pixels when a visitor lands on the page. These contain <strong>identifiable technical signatures</strong> — script URLs, JavaScript namespaces, and widget code — that reveal which third-party tools are installed.
            <br /><br />
            The scanner fetches your store's public HTML and cross-references it against a database of <strong>30+ common Shopify apps</strong>, then matches detected apps against typical subscription pricing to generate your estimated monthly spend and efficiency score:
            <ul>
              <li>Script URLs referencing third-party CDN services</li>
              <li>Embedded tracking pixels and analytics widgets</li>
              <li>JavaScript namespaces and global variables used by Shopify apps</li>
              <li>External API endpoint references in page source</li>
              <li>Inline configuration objects specific to known platforms</li>
            </ul>
            Apps like <a href="/triple-whale-alternative">Triple Whale</a>, <a href="/elevar-alternative">Elevar</a>, and <a href="/analyzify-alternative">Analyzify</a> each leave distinct script fingerprints that the scanner identifies in real time.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

